    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Possible duplicate : <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14818348/will-android-java-support-lambda-expression-in-java-8\">will android java support lambda expression in java 8?</a></p>\n\n<p>In the possible duplicate question, kapep answered this (read the full answer for more details) :</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Android doesn't use Oracle's Java SE versions, it's based on parts of the Apache Harmony project so it doesn't even support Java 7. Harmony is not actively developed any more and won't support 1.7.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>So I think you can forget new features of Oracle Java version for Android development and follow the Android API (not the Oracle one).</p>\n"
  }, {
